16/02/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police have identified about 30 people who allegedly participated in clashes over a controversial Skopje cultural project, media reported on Tuesday (February 15th).
Eight people, including two policemen, were injured on Sunday when ethnic Macedonian and Albanian youth brawled over plans to build a museum-church on the site of the Skopje Fortress.
Meanwhile, the Dutch Foreign Ministry has investigated allegations that Artan Grubi, an employee of the Dutch Embassy in Skopje, and the leader of the NGO Wake Up, helped organise the protests.
Concluding that he violated rules, Grubi has been suspended from work.
(Makfax, Sitel, MIA - 15/02/11)
